HEADWORD: Lecherous
<hw>Lech"er*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Like a lecher;
addicted to lewdness; excessively lustful; -- used mostly of men;</def>
<specif>also,</specif> <def>lust-provoking.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧A
<xex>lecherous</xex> thing is wine.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Chaucer.</au> --
<wordforms><wf>Lech"er*ous*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Lech"er*ous*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>lecherousness</ent>⟦br⟧
